OL,3,CThe economy is turning a corner - but
OL,4,Cvery slowly
OL,6,FThe truth is the UK has been stuck in
OL,7,Fa low growth rut since 2008 and, as a
OL,8,Fresult, wages have barely grown.
OL,10,FBetween 1992 and 2007 - under John
OL,11,FMajor and Tony Blair - Gross Domestic
OL,12,FProduct (GDP) per person in the UK
OL,13,Feconomy increased by 45.9%.
OL,15,FIn the last 15 years since - Gordon
OL,16,FBrown, David Cameron, Theresa May,
OL,17,FBoris Johnson, Liz Truss and Rishi
OL,18,FSunak - it has grown by just 4.3%.
