OL,3,CThe economy is turning a corner - but
OL,4,Cvery slowly
OL,6,FHad the economy continued on its pre-
OL,7,F2008 trend, the Resolution Foundation
OL,8,Fcalculates that the average worker
OL,9,Fwould be #14,000 a year better off.
OL,11,FSlow growth is a serious problem. The
OL,12,FUK is not the only wealthy country to
OL,13,Fexperience "stagnation" but our strain
OL,14,Flooks particularly virulent.
OL,16,FAll of the parties in this election
OL,17,Fare promising to grow the economy. All
OL,18,Fof them promise better jobs, better
OL,19,Fpay and higher living standards.
